meanings.definition: To defeat in a competition or contest
meanings.sent1: She outdueled her opponent in the chess tournament.
meanings.sent2: The champion outdueled all the challengers in the race.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outdueled the birds in gathering the most nuts.
meanings.sent4: His determination outdueled any obstacles in his path.
meanings.sent5: The sun outdueled the clouds, shining brightly in the sky.

meanings.definition: To surpass in skill or performance
meanings.sent1: He outdueled his classmates in solving the math problems.
meanings.sent2: The acrobat outdueled everyone with her amazing stunts.
meanings.sent3: The chef outdueled expectations with his delicious new recipe.
meanings.sent4: Her creativity outdueled all others in the art competition.
meanings.sent5: The athlete outdueled his own record, setting a new personal best.
